.TH "_pci_add_cap_save_buffer" 9 "_pci_add_cap_save_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_pci_add_cap_save_buffer \- allocate buffer for saving given capability registers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _pci_add_cap_save_buffer
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u16 cap "  ","
.BI "bool extended "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the PCI device
.IP "cap" 12
the capability to allocate the buffer for
.IP "extended" 12
Standard or Extended capability ID
.IP "size" 12
requested size of the buffer
